b"it certainly be multi-user what i have see from the march beta be that it yet come with the stuff which exploit multi-user feature i remember somebody from m state that it allow two user share one gui my interpretation of this be that one user per console but all the networking and rpc base stuff you want i believe ftp and rlogin deamons for nt system will come from third party somebody already have a beta version of an unsecure ftpd on the net there be no reason why one can not write a posix base shell like csh on unix for remote logins in general i like nt when i checked it out it slow compare to win3.1 just like any other real o the beta version although be slow botts up much faster than my sun workstation window subsystem also start up a lot faster than x window i believe bill gate be right when he state that nt be not for everybody after play around with it for a while i be convince if i own a busines use a `` business computer '' from ibm or some other establish vendor i would consider move to nt platform because it would provide a much cheaper solution if you be run sql server etc. it provide the robustness such an application require on the other hand if you like your do game more or less forget about nt you can always boot to do but in general that defeat the purpose of use nt most of nt 's feature be visible in a networked environment and in such an environment you reboot your machine at will for personal use i would rather wait for the win32 base window release whatever you name it than jump to nt bandwagon i expect most application will keep on use win16 until win32 becomes widely available"

to publicize their software release inform user of update version and to increase their instal base of user those search for specific window software will benefit by have a complete list of available software available at their fingertip complete with feature list current price and any other relevant information window software author may submit entry to window shareware monthly in the follow manner 1. compose a short summary of the function of the software include all special feature which be unique to your product and which set it apart from other program in the genre be sure to include specific detail such a the current release version where the software be available how much the registration fee cost how much disk space be require any special requirement e.g sound card or vbrun200.dll etc how the author may be contact etc because text be highly compressible the summary may be a long a be necessary however it be best to keep it short a good guideline be a single screenful of 12-point text at 640x480 resolution order form and other such addendum may be include if desire all submission whould be in plain text ascii format format will be exactly a it be submit i will simply cut and paste text file into a help author system if you require special format convention such a boldface text or italic or a large font size indicate so clearly within the text file for best result use window notepad to create the .txt file 2. include up to 100k of windows-format .bmp bitmap screen-shots which display the working or special feature of each program special case render application for example which require 256-color bitmap may submit up to 250k of .bmp file all other should observe the 100k limit and use 16-color format for maximum compatiblity with the software which will be use to create the wsm .hlp file stefan olson 's help writer's assistant for window please save the bitmap with window paintbrush or wingif 3. include a 16-color .bmp of the program 's icon .ico file many program be available to convert .ico to .bmp format or window paintbrush may be use the .bmp will be embed in the summary text 4. double-check for spell error format correction etc 5. compress the .txt file the .bmp of the program icon and any additional .bmps into a single file use pkzip any version 6. submit the entry by uuencoding the .zipfile and e-mailing it to daa7365 require or a new version be release complete the above procedure again send all submission to the tamuts address and any comment suggestion criticism to daa7365 rigel.tamu.edu all entry receive before the deadline will be include in the subsequent edition of wsm the editor will not be held responsible for any error and we reserve the right to make change to the entry wsm be not limited to shareware/freeware software a special area will be devote to commercially available window 3.x and nt software commercial software author should follow the same step above with the exception of the limitation on size the .txt file and .bmps may be a large a require and a large a be practical for transmission over phone line there be no charge for the publishing of either shareware/freeware or commercial product entry advertisement for computer hardware software bulletin board etc may be submit a well again the same procedure apply with the exception of the size limitation there be no charge for advertising space the first ten advertisement submit each month will be include subsequent submission will not be include due to size constraint wsm be currently look for person willing to devote the time to author column within wsm a c/c++ program section a visual basic section and two windows-specific opinion/advice column be envision all work will be on a voluntary basis if you wish an extra button for configuration purpose one annoy feature be the title window that be first present when it be run you must press a key not a mouse button for the thing to go away also it would have it be quite time consume to set thing up with workspace 1.10 all but the first workspace be initially empty with workshift 1.6 you need to take `` snapshot '' of how you want each of your workspace to look like i.e what application they contain also the main window be quite large but this do allow you to have a small view of what be in each workspace with workspace 1.10 there be no facility for contains a few other goody a well a a workspace manager other goody include `` backmenu '' which provide a pop-up root menu when you press a certain mouse button just like in x-windows the menu be totally configurable offering unlimited depth of cascade menu which be provide quite handy access to application you could say it be a menu-based alternative to the program manager also bundle in `` backdesk.zip '' be a program call `` wrun '' which allows you to run window application from a do shell under window instead of use the file manager to run application the actual workspace manager be call bigdesk 2.30. bigdesk work quite differently to the other two workspace manager in that it provide a certain number of disjoint and separate workspace in fact it basically enlarges your desktop by a configurable amount and you choose which region of the desktop you want your screen to focus in on this mean you can have window overlap between different view region unlike the first two workspace manager in which each workspace be isolated from the other one the bigdesk control window allows to to move window around your enlarge desktop basically the control window provide a small scale view of your view area while your actual computer screen provide a large scale or blow-up of a particular section"

b"from the window resource toolkit for win4workgroups add an entry to your `` system.ini '' file under the nonwindowsapp section commandenvsize=nnnn '' this set the command.com env size where nnnn must either be 0 or between 160 and 32768. a value of 0 disables the set if this value be too small or too big it be round up to 160 or down to 32768. if the value be less than the current size of the actual environment this set be disabled a if it be 0. if you specify the environment size in a pif file for command.com the pif set override this set the default be 0 with msdos version earlier than 3.2. otherwise the default value be the /e option in the shell= command in config.sys to set this value you must edit your system.ini and reboot '' i have use this entry a well a rely on the default /e from the config.sys shell= line and both give large environment if you use one of these then the environment pass by window to each new do box be just a little bit big than the environment _variables_ present when window be start no matter how big the do env be when window start it truncates all unused space except for a few byte this should allow your batch file to run but your mileage may vary"

b"gawd i love window probably want to delete any damage executables and reload them fresh data file should be examine and repair not stupid smartdrive cache thing and window also run a swap file which may contain data also all of this be pretty risky stuff in a pc environment a reasonably accurate prediction ... here 's a brief description of how do store file there be three piece to a file the directory entry the fat chain and the data area you can think of these a a sheet of line notebook paper a sheet of graph paper and a stack of 3x5 card the directory entry notebook paper hold the file name actual size and first cluster number it also hold some other information not important right now the file allocation table fat chain graph paper tell where to find the actual data each square of graph paper hold a number if the number be zero the cluster associate with this box be available if it hold a `` magic '' number it be either the last piece of a file or a bad unuseable spot on the disk any other number tell which cluster contains the next section of the file the data area 3x5 card be where the actual information be store the data area be organize a cluster of a fix size storage be doled out in `` chunk '' of one cluster each in your case one cluster be 2048 byte a a cluster be fill another be allocate to read a file you first look at the directory entry to get the start cluster number now you read the data from that cluster next look at the fat entry for the cluster you just read this will tell you the cluster number for the next chunk of the file naturally these number be usually sequential but they can jump around and even go backwards continue reading one cluster at a time a you walk this chain through the fat until you hit the marker which say the last cluster in the file chkdsk be the do utility that check the sanity and coherence of the directory and the fat and can bludgeon most flaw into submission it have any intelligence so you have to double-check anything it `` fix '' now let 's do a bit of a post-mortem all of these file have size accord to the fat which match the size report in their directory entry chkdsk /f will alter the directory entry to match the fat size in other word the directory entry for cvpic.exe may say the file be 64,877 byte long but chkdsk found a fat chain of 43 cluster attach to it my number obviously be make up disk space be found which be allocate in the fat but be not attach to any directory entry chkdsk /f give you the option of convert these '' lose chain '' to file you can then examine the file file0000.chk through file0223.chk and rename or discard them or if you tell chkdsk _not_ to convert them to file then those cluster will simply be marked `` available '' in the fat ... these file be both reference the _same_ data cluster obviously one of them at least must be wrong interest to note that c \\386spart.par be your window swap file ... to fix this you should copy each cross-linked file to a new name this will `` fix '' the cross-link by give the file unique data space now delete the cross-linked file examine the copy and try to assemble them properly good luck hint `` miss piece '' be likely to be found in those `` lose chain '' at the top ... your disk be pretty close to full this may be the actual cause of the problem perhaps window need to expand it swapfile by an amount which exceed available disk space ... in any case the short summary be that something trash your fat there be utility that can mirror your fat and help repair damage after something like this but you have to run them _before_ the problem occurs sorry -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- gordon s. hlavenka cgordon vpnet.chi.il.us vote straight ticket procrastination party dec. 3rd --"

b'this entirely true it be true that truetype font be large than their atm counterpart but atm font *do* get minimal compression run stacker 3.0 report generator i get file type compression ratio -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- *.ttf truetype 1.4:1.0 *.pfb atm 1.1:1.0 *.pfm atm metric 11.8:1.0 although the metric file be small they compress quite largely and a you can see even the regular .pfb file have *some* compression so do the math on one such comparitive font file ttf time 83260 bytes/1.4 59471 byte compress pfb time 51549 bytes/1.1 46862 byte compress you still win out even if the atm time font ** compress your mileage may vary depend on compression program'

'' be the amount of virtual address space that the virtual memory manager will create and this be a function of the amount of free memory that you have when window start in the 386enh section of system.ini you can specify a parameter pageovercommit=multiplier the follow description be from the window resource kit this entry specifies the multiplier what determines the amount of linear address space the vmm will create for the system which be compute by round up the amount of available physical memory to the near 4 mb and then multiply that value by the value specify for pageovercommit= increase this value increase the amount of available linear address space cause the size of data structure to increase this also increase page activity proportionately and can slow down the system you can specify a value between 1 and 20. the default be 4. to change this entry you must edit system.ini"

b"i think you may be chase the wrong problem i think it be the function overload at all -- i do that sort of thing all of the time in bc++ without a hitch the big problem i have encounter in port mfc to bc++ be that fact that mfc _depends_ on a couple of invalid c++ assumption i have never gotten the _entire_ ctrltest app to run under bc++ but the reason be that m make some bad assumption about the order in which static/global object be initialize i.e some object be get access before they be initialize the problem be in the owner-draw menu code somewhere -- if you comment out that section all other piece of ctrltest work fine two other major gotchas i have found use mfc under bc++ the cfile :openflags enum us hard-coded number for the open mode rather than the manifest constant define in fcntrl.h which differ between msc and bc all of the mfc collection class depend on another bad c++ assumption -- that a reference to a base object can use be in place of a reference to a derive object true for pointer not for reference i be sure there be other problem along the same line but i have not encounter them yet i have not see mfc 2.0 yet but i hope that some of these will be address if they be not all of ms's hype about portability to other vendor 's compiler will be just that"

b'... this be a common problem with highly complex truetype font microsoft admits to a problem with old version of the postscript printer driver but found it to be pretty generic you can get around the problem by adjust the parameter outlinethreshold in the truetype section of win.ini this entry specifies the number of pels-per-em at which window will render truetype font a outline font instead of a bitmap font the default be 256. generally be able to get font to work by set outlinethreshold=160 depend on your printer resolution and the point size you be use you may need a different value the window resource kit warns against go above 300. presumably that might cause font to print a square box or something -| not smile'

b"i have normal procomm plus for do but be consider buying the window version ... .it get really great review in computer shopper i have a friend who connects to the mainframe and unix machine here use it but the screen seem to have a problem keep up with the modem ... .he have a 14,400 modem on a 486 50 mhz machine i see it have trouble keep up his pcplus for do work great re what to do after the high speed modem arrives edition 01 apr 93 this article applies only to window 3.0 and 3.1 and not to nt os/2 or do apps not run under window one of the unadvertised limitation of most current window pc be that their rs-232c serial com performance be seriously deficient almost everyone who purchase a high-speed modem v.32bis v.32 pep or hst discovers the problem the first time they try to download a file or accept an incoming fax at 9600+ after upgrade the modem overrun and retry error abound even when the only active application be the datacomm or fax program if the transfer completes at all it may take even longer than with the old 2400bps modem there be three reason for the problem 1. the universal asynchronous receiver/transmitters uarts use in most pc be primitive ns8250 device with single-byte fifo buffer if the operating system/driver can not read and flush each character at high interrupt rate the next incoming character overwrites the fifo and the previous one be lose do be a fairly single-minded environment during datacomm can usually keep up window 2. window have more operating system overhead than plain do and interrupt often take longer to service overrun be much more likely than under do a soon a you report to your pc/modem vendor that you be lose data you may be advise that `` you need to upgrade to a 16550 '' more likely since there seem to be a conspiracy of ignorance about this issue get no useful advice at all most of the store-front and mail-order source i spoke with in attempt to solve my own problem have never heard the term `` 16550 '' and many even know what a uart be 3. even your pc have ns16550a uarts and ps/2 's do or if you can upgrade your mother/com board or add a new com board you may still experience error and overrun because the standard microsoft window com driver take full advantage of the 16550. window 3.1 be improve in this regard over 3.0 but i still recommend a driver upgrade application like procomm+/win which be what i use can not get around this problem by themselves if you have a modem card you may not have a problem a the modem part of the card can be design to be aware of the state of the uart and avoid overrun it however i want to bet that the card designer be that clever and will insist on a 16550 uart if i ever buy a modem card some modem card even have conventional uarts but if they be to work with standard window driver they need to simulate one use msd.exe below to see what the modem card be or be pretend to be the hardware situation the uarts on most pc com port be base on national semiconductor ns8250 or ns16450 chip or megacells inside vlsi chip where you replace them you can id the uart type on your system by run the microsoft diagnostic program \\windows\\msd.exe be sure to run it in do *before* bring up window the window serial api may prevent msd from accurately identify a 16550 if you run it from a window do prompt the ns16550 uart have separate 16-byte transmit and receive fifo with configurable trigger level and can run reliably at clock rate up to 460,800 bps although with current modem technology there 's no point in push your luck by go over 115,200 bps the 16550 have short access cycle time than the 16450 or 8250. the 16550 also have dma capability but it be not clear that any pc driver ever use this for more technical info see national semiconductor application note an-491 so what uart component do you have try to locate the uart on your mother board multi-function i/o card com board or isa/mca modem card if you find a socketed component with the number `` 8250 '' or `` 16450 '' your com port be probably bury in vlsi and you be able to perform a chip replacement if you can disable your vlsi com port a i chose to do you can at least add an aftermarket com board if you have one or more socketed 8250 or 16450 chip you can buy plug-in ns16550afn or pc16c550cn low power cmos version ic from several supplier typically for 9 to 15 each the `` n '' chip be the normal 40-pin dual-in-line package other style be available but avoid any ns16550 chip without the `` a '' the 16c550c be presumably all ok early n chip have bug although national will reportedly exchange those of their own manufacture for free clone chip be available from various ic maker other than national the manual for the turbocom driver state support for the follow apparently equivalent chip national semiconductor 16550a 16551 16552 chip technology 82c607 texas instrument t16c550a silicon system 73m550 vlsi 16c550 turbocom warns about the pre- '' a '' ns16550 and western digital 16c550 say that problem have be report with early ibm ps/2 55sx and 70 system ibm reportedly will upgrade them if you do n't have socketed 8250/16450 chip need to buy an after- market com or multi-function board if this be a modem card situation you may be hose to add a new com or multi-function card need to either disable the com1/2 port s you be replace or re-assign them to com3/4 although watch out for irq conflict without turbocom although cheaper card be available in the interest of get the problem solve quickly i elect buy the modular circuit technology mct-aio+ card from jdr microdevices 2233 samaritan drive san jose ca 95124 800 538-5000 voice u 408 559-1200 voice other 800 538-5005 fax u the mct-aio+ and the `` '' be important sell for 89.95 it be an 8-bit isa card provide port type connector address and irq comment com db9m com 1,2,3 irq 2,3,4,5 ns16550afn in socket com ribbon com 2,3,4 irq 2,3,4,5 ns16550afn in socket parallel db25f lpt1,2,3 irq 5,7 game ribbon the kit include a ribbon cable and db25f connector for the secondary com port a ribbon cable/connector for the game port two bulkhead plate for the ribbon-based connector and a 9f-to-25f adaptor cable each port can be individually disabled and the com port have tx rx rts ct dtr dcd and dsr jumper jdr also sell a super-i/o m-f card that also have ide i have heard from several people about less expensive m-f i/o card with 16550s tsd system 407 331-9130 19.95 for the card plus 9.95 per 16550. greenfield trading and distributor 518 271-2473 voice 518 271-7811 fax their card be 33 w/one 16550 45 w/2 and they sell 16550afns for 13 r s data system inc. 820 east highway 434 longwood fl 32750 phone 407 331-1424 fax 407 331-8606 2com/lpt/game card w/2 16550s for 39 i have no personal experience with any of the firm except jdr meanwhile back at the mct card from jdr ... i only need two serial port and be run out of irqs on my pc so i disabled my built-in vlsi-based 8250 port however with the turbocom driver below i could have set the internals a com3 and 4 use irq share the software situation simply upgrade to 16550 uarts will not completely solve common overrun problem the standard m serial driver take full advantage of the 16550. the window 3.0 driver be even less capable and the window 3.1 driver have the follow limitation they enable only the receive fifo and only at rate above 2400 bps they never enable the transmit fifo which result in an interrupt rate of 10x during uploads they set the trigger level at 14 byte too high easy for 2 more byte to arrive before the driver can read the fifo the port menu of the control panel only allows speed up to 19200. with a v.32bis modem sparse data and text can easily compress 3:1 or more suggest that a host dte connect rate of 57,600 bps would be effective the api accept rate above `` cbr_128000 '' the api let do program know there be a 16550 there and even if it do do program that 16550-aware get little benefit from a 16550 port with the standard driver they allow irq share for com3,4 the bios initialize com3,4 properly in many system window provide no workaround for apps that provide port speed option above 19200 bps these problem be reportedly not solve in window nt or do 6.0 and may or may not be address in any window release after 3.1 but before 4.0 rumor suggest they `` may '' be solve in window `` 4.0 '' you can get replacement driver that solve all of those problem by buying a copy of `` turbocom '' current version 1.2 from bio-engineering research pacific commware division 180 beacon hill lane ashland or 97520-9701 503 482-2744 voice 503 482-2627 fax 503 482-2633 bb mcimail 344-5374 compuserve 71521,760 price be around 50 a i recall bio-eng be not set up to accept credit card so i have to send a check egghead and 1-800-software list turbocom but a far a i know they stock it bio be not a software company per se they apparently need reliable hi-speed serial connection for an in-house instrument application write their own driver discover a market for it revise it to be a general purpose com driver suite they recently upgraded it for window 3.1. it be run-time license i now have my host dte connect rate set to 57,600 bps most of my datacomm apps and i be have zero problem with downloads i routinely see transfer rate that exceed 2,000 bps i be also use 115,200 bps when link an hp95lx to my pc with lossless bi-directional i/o uploads to various remote system be another matter because many host be still use antique uarts and driver note that 19200 be still the high rate that the window 3.1 port menu in control panel will allow in configure a com port turbocom get around this by allow you to specify on each port a factor that will set the real uart rate to a multiple of the rate pass through the window apis and dialog box i also have cts/rts hardware flow control enable and i suggest that you do the same even if you only ever transfer 7-bit ascii data xon/xoff be not a sufficiently reliable method of flow control the informal dec standard for xon/xoff hysteresis be that the sender may transmit another 16 yes sixteen byte after receipt of the xoff from the receive system or device the 16 byte fifo in the 16550 be clearly not big enough to let u rely exclusively on xon/xoff a well-respected datacomm engineer have inform me that the 16550 's really do cts/rts all by itself in the dos/windows environment so use data rate above 115,200 may still be risky even with hardware flow control a 16550 with turbocom can still experience overrun in very busy system with lot of apps run and serious swap in progress if this be your situation you may need to buy a co-processed com board but this will cost you more than a 16550/turbocom upgrade a review of two such board and a review of turbocom can be found in the feb'93 issue of `` window source '' magazine i suggest try a 16550/turbocom upgrade first and experiment with process priority and time slice if you be a `` power user '' whose thrash system still run into comm problem closing soapbox comment the state of rs-232c serial datacomm support be an embarrassment across the computer industry because it be the old standard i/o interface the job of design hardware and write software often seem to be assign to the least senior or low ranked engineer at computer company the design of the average serial port be at least ten year behind the state of the art in my last job with a major workstation vendor i lobby for improve serial port when they be do the initial design of a new system that family of machine be subsequently introduce with 16550 port however this be the exception few computer company seem to have any champion for decent i/o you may a well learn what you can about serial i/o because this situation show no sign of improve soon when v.fast arrives i expect cry of outrage from window user world-wide whose 8250 pc `` sort of '' work today with v.32 but will fail miserably with v.fast without a hardware-buffered uart like the 16550 and without software driver that use that uart to best advantage a v.fast modem will be a waste of money regard 1001-a for window nt name comp.os.ms-windows.nt.misc status unmoderated purpose miscellaneous non-programming discussion about use window nt include issue such a security networking feature console mode and window 3.1 win16 compatability rationale microsoft nt be the new member of the microsoft window family of operating system or operating environment for those who wish to argue about the meaning of an `` o '' the family range from modular window through window 3.1 and window for workgroups to window nt at the high end to date microsoft have ship over 50,000 beta copy and pre-release sdks of window nt -- the actual release be slat for may/june '93 while window nt have an entirely new design internally it share an application program interface with the other member of the window family it win32 api include the win16 api use in win- dows 3.1 and the win32s api subset win32 less thread networking and security can be use to create 32-bit application for window 3.1. the user interface be also practically identical to that of window 3.1 with the addition of logins and a few other feature it us program manager file manager and other applet and generally pre- sent an identical appearance to the user many of the announce window nt application be port of exist window 3.1 apps and nt also run exist 3.1 application thus it appear logical that window nt should share the follow group with the other member of the window family comp.os.ms-windows.apps comp.os.ms-windows.programmer.tools comp.os.ms-windows.programmer.misc comp.os.ms-windows.programmer.win32 the follow group be also clearly applicable to window nt a well a window 3.1 comp.os.ms-windows.announce comp.os.ms-windows.advocacy in conclusion the only clear argument for the separation of the window 3.1 and window nt hierarchy
